        <head xml:id="la30px-bbb679-Hd1e104">Final</head>
        <p xml:id="la30px-bbb679-d1e106">
          This is, most illustrious sirs, all that I, in forty-nine years which I have seen evil done in the Indies, and thirty-four years in which I have studied law, feel. I will soon give the proof and corroboration of these aforementioned thirty propositions, in Spanish and Latin to Your Highness. Then the title, that the Monarchs of Castille and León have over the universal and sovereign empire of the New World of the Indian Oceans, will appear founded, proved and corroborated. In this I hope to do Your Majesty, and the kings to come hereafter in these kingdoms, a not small service. 
        </p>
        <p xml:id="la30px-bbb679-d1e132">
          Printed in Sevilla, in the house of Sebastián Trujillo.  
        </p>
